---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = "July 9, 2026";
---
<Layout title="Terms of Service" description="The terms governing your use of Cornfed Bucks.">
  <section class="legal">
    <div class="wrap legal__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Terms of Service</p>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of cornfedbucks.com (the "Site"), operated by
        Cornfed Bucks. By accessing or using the Site, you agree to these Terms. If you don't agree,
        please don't use the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Content Is for Informational Purposes Only</h2>
      <p>
        Cornfed Bucks provides general information about whitetail deer hunting, hunting gear, and
        firearm regulations relevant to straight-wall cartridge hunting. This content is provided for
        informational and educational purposes only and does not constitute legal, safety, or
        professional advice.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hunting regulations change and vary by state, and sometimes by county or zone within a
        state.</strong> Always verify current legal requirements — including legal calibers, case-length
        limits, season dates, and zone boundaries — directly with your state's Department of Natural
        Resources or equivalent agency before you hunt. Cornfed Bucks makes reasonable efforts to keep
        regulation-related content accurate as of its publish date, but we cannot guarantee that content
        reflects the most current rule changes, and we are not responsible for consequences arising from
        reliance on outdated or inaccurate information found on this Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Firearm and Ammunition Content</h2>
      <p>
        Any discussion of firearms, ammunition, ballistics, or ammunition selection is provided for
        general informational purposes. You are solely responsible for the safe and legal use, storage,
        and handling of any firearm or ammunition, and for complying with all applicable federal, state,
        and local laws.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate Relationships</h2>
      <p>
        Cornfed Bucks is a participant in the Amazon Services LLC Associates Program and may participate
        in other affiliate programs, meaning we may earn a commission from qualifying purchases made
        through links on this Site, at no additional cost to you. See our
        <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a> for details. Product recommendations
        reflect our own editorial judgment; commissions do not influence which products we choose to
        feature.
      </p>

      <h2>No Warranty</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and its content are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or
        implied, including but not limited to accuracy, completeness, or fitness for a particular
        purpose.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, Cornfed Bucks and its operator shall not be liable for
        any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Site or
        reliance on any content published on it.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        The Site contains links to third-party websites, including retailers and affiliate partners. We
        do not control and are not responsible for the content, policies, or practices of any
        third-party site.
      </p>

      <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        Content published on this Site, including text, graphics, and diagrams, is the property of
        Cornfed Bucks unless otherwise noted, and may not be reproduced without permission.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an
        updated "Last updated" date. Continued use of the Site after changes are posted constitutes
        acceptance of the revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms can be directed to <a href="mailto:nick@cornfedbucks.com">nick@cornfedbucks.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal { padding: 3.5rem 0 5rem; }
  .legal__inner { max-width: 680px; }
  .legal h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .legal .updated {
    font-family: var(--font-tag);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal p, .legal li {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .legal ul { padding-left: 1.3rem; }
  .legal li { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
</style>
